For those who wants to install it permanently follow this instructions ( to do as sudo ) :

If you do not already have a dir for your personnal scripts : 
	mkdir ~/bin;

Edit ~/.bashrc :
	gedit ~/.bashrc;

Go to the end of your file and paste : 
	 export PATH=$PATH:~/bin;

Then : 
	cp make_proto_cpp ~/bin/;
	mkdir /usr/local/man/man8;
	cp make_proto_cpp.8.gz /usr/local/man/man8/;
	source ~/.bashrc;

Here you go, you can now use the command make_proto_cpp, and find it's 
man page by typing in your shell : 
	man make_proto_cpp
